Before venturing into a general proof, we list out things which stand corrected in light of our work in context of Bianchi-I model, and in fact, anisotropic models in general.
\begin{enumerate}
\item Unitarity guarantees that there is no discrepancy between Many World inpterpretation/ Copenhagen interpretation and de Broglie-Bohm interpretation. Alvarenga et. al. \cite{alvarenga3} argued that there is a  nonequivalence between the two interpretations owing to non-unitarity of the model, which, according to them, is due to hyperbolic structure of kinetic term in Wheeler-deWitt equation. It deserved mention that self-adjoint Hamiltonian leads to no discrepency between Many World inpterpretation/ Copenhagen interpretation and de Broglie-Bohm interpretation is a necessary and sufficient condition \cite{alvarenga3}. Hence, the conclusion regarding the discrepancy made by Alvarenga et. al. is now corrected in the light of the present work.

\item A related cosmological implication is regarding late time bahviour of Bianchi-I universe. Alvarenga et. al. found that the expectation value of the scale factor reveals an isotropic universe in late time when calculated in the spirit of Many World interpretation while bohmian trajectories revealed anisotropy is present even in late times. Now that there is no such discrepency, two interpretation should yield identical results. In \cite{sridip4}, we have been able to show that isotropy can be achieved at late times for Bianchi-I.
\end{enumerate} 

